{"id": "c0c0c0c0-0091-0000-0000-000000000000", "name": "System Layers", "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3", "created": 1741219200000, "modified": 1773243817663, "content": {"description": [":doc", [":p", {"s": "Hobson has three layers: the "}, [":strong", {"s": "kernel"}], {"s": ", the "}, [":strong", {"s": "viewport"}], {"s": ", and "}, [":strong", {"s": "userland"}], {"s": ". Each layer builds on the one below it. Understanding this split is the key to knowing where things live and where to look when you want to change something."}], [":h2", {"s": "The Three Layers"}], [":table", [":thead", [":tr", [":th", {"s": "Layer"}], [":th", {"s": "Role"}], [":th", {"s": "Can you modify it?"}]]], [":tbody", [":tr", [":td", [":strong", {"s": "Kernel"}]], [":td", {"s": "Data, events, code loading"}], [":td", {"s": "Possible but risky — use "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "33333333-7777-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "safe mode"}], {"s": " to recover"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":strong", {"s": "Viewport"}]], [":td", {"s": "Rendering, navigation, all UI"}], [":td", {"s": "Yes — these are regular items, hot-reloadable"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":strong", {"s": "Userland"}]], [":td", {"s": "Views, libraries, types, your data"}], [":td", {"s": "Yes — this is where you work"}]]]], [":h2", {"s": "Kernel"}], [":p", {"s": "The kernel is the smallest possible runtime that makes everything else work. It has no UI (except a "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "33333333-7777-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "safe mode"}], {"s": " fallback screen). It provides four things:"}], [":table", [":thead", [":tr", [":th", {"s": "Responsibility"}], [":th", {"s": "Module"}], [":th", {"s": "What it does"}]]], [":tbody", [":tr", [":td", [":strong", {"s": "Storage"}]], [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "33333333-2222-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "kernel:storage"}]], [":td", {"s": "Persists items in IndexedDB, validates type chains, handles queries"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":strong", {"s": "Events"}]], [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "33333333-1111-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "kernel:core"}]], [":td", {"s": "Type-hierarchy-aware event bus — "}, [":code", {"s": "item:updated"}], {"s": ", "}, [":code", {"s": "item:created"}], {"s": ", "}, [":code", {"s": "item:deleted"}], {"s": ", and custom events"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":strong", {"s": "Code loading"}]], [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "33333333-4444-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "kernel:module-system"}]], [":td", [":code", {"s": "api.require('name')"}], {"s": " loads code items as ES modules with caching and circular dependency detection"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":strong", {"s": "Bootstrap"}]], [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "33333333-1111-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "kernel:core"}]], [":td", {"s": "Initializes storage, applies "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "33333333-8888-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "styles"}], {"s": ", emits "}, [":code", {"s": "kernel:boot-complete"}], {"s": " so the viewport can take over"}]]]], [":p", {"s": "The kernel also defines the base "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "33333333-1111-0000-0000-000000000000#code?region=createAPI"}, {"s": "API object"}], {"s": " that all other code uses — item CRUD, events, "}, [":code", {"s": "require()"}], {"s": ", parent-child operations. This is the API you see in the "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "c0c0c0c0-0008-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "REPL"}], {"s": "."}], [":p", {"s": "The kernel's design principle: "}, [":strong", {"s": "if it can be built as a userland item, it should be."}], {"s": " See "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "c0c0c0c0-0001-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "Kernel"}], {"s": " for the full philosophy."}], [":h2", {"s": "Viewport"}], [":p", {"s": "The viewport is the application shell — everything you see on screen. It is built entirely from regular items (not kernel code), but most users will never need to modify it."}], [":p", {"s": "The viewport handles two broad concerns:"}], [":h3", {"s": "Rendering"}], [":p", {"s": "The "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "f1111111-0008-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "viewport-rendering"}], {"s": " library is the rendering engine. It turns items into DOM:"}], [":ul", [":li", [":p", [":strong", {"s": "View resolution"}], {"s": " — decides which view to use for an item (preference hierarchy, type chain lookup, fallback). See "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000004"}, {"s": "Views & Rendering"}], {"s": "."}]], [":li", [":p", [":strong", {"s": "Render instance registry"}], {"s": " — tracks every rendered DOM node so the system can do partial re-renders when items change"}]], [":li", [":p", [":strong", {"s": "Enriched API"}], {"s": " — adds rendering methods ("}, [":code", {"s": "renderItem"}], {"s": ", "}, [":code", {"s": "rerenderItem"}], {"s": ", "}, [":code", {"s": "navigate"}], {"s": ", "}, [":code", {"s": "getViews"}], {"s": ", etc.) on top of the kernel's base API. Views receive this enriched API; the REPL gets only the kernel primitives."}]], [":li", [":p", [":strong", {"s": "Reactive re-rendering"}], {"s": " — listens for "}, [":code", {"s": "item:updated"}], {"s": " events and re-renders affected views, filtered by "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "c0c0c0c0-0062-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "selectors"}], {"s": " so only relevant changes trigger work"}]]], [":h3", {"s": "Chrome"}], [":p", {"s": "The remaining viewport items provide the application frame:"}], [":table", [":thead", [":tr", [":th", {"s": "Item"}], [":th", {"s": "What it does"}]]], [":tbody", [":tr", [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "f1111111-0002-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "viewport-manager"}]], [":td", {"s": "Navigation (URL sync, history, root item management)"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "bd74da77-a459-454a-b001-48685d4b536d"}, {"s": "viewport-view"}]], [":td", {"s": "The top-level view — renders chrome, decorates items, manages selection highlighting"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "f1111111-0001-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "selection-manager"}]], [":td", {"s": "Tracks which item is selected and its parent"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "f1111111-0004-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "keyboard-shortcuts"}]], [":td", {"s": "Global shortcuts (Ctrl+K, Ctrl+?)"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "f1111111-0005-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "item-palette"}]], [":td", {"s": "The Ctrl+K search/navigation dialog"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "f1111111-0003-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "repl-ui"}]], [":td", {"s": "The REPL panel (Ctrl+\\\\)"}]], [":tr", [":td", [":item-ref", {"s": "f1111111-0006-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "help-dialog"}]], [":td", {"s": "The Ctrl+? shortcut reference"}]]]], [":p", {"s": "See "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "c0c0c0c0-0033-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "Viewport"}], {"s": " for full details."}], [":h2", {"s": "Userland"}], [":p", {"s": "Everything else. This is where the system's real value lives:"}], [":ul", [":li", [":p", [":strong", {"s": "[Views](item://aaaaaaaa-0000-0000-0000-000000000000)"}], {"s": " — how items get displayed (note view, spatial canvas, list view, etc.)"}]], [":li", [":p", [":strong", {"s": "[Libraries](item://66666666-0000-0000-0000-000000000000)"}], {"s": " — reusable code loaded via "}, [":code", {"s": "api.require()"}]]], [":li", [":p", [":strong", {"s": "[Type definitions](item://11111111-0000-0000-0000-000000000000)"}], {"s": " — what kinds of items exist (note, tag, container, etc.)"}]], [":li", [":p", [":strong", {"s": "Your items"}], {"s": " — notes, tasks, workspaces, anything you create"}]]], [":p", {"s": "Userland items are fully inspectable and modifiable. You can change how notes render, create new types, add libraries — the system is designed for this. See "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000002"}, {"s": "Core Concepts"}], {"s": " for how items, types, views, and libraries fit together."}], [":h2", {"s": "How They Connect"}], [":p", {"s": "At boot, the flow is:"}], [":ol", [":li", [":p", {"s": "The "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "c0c0c0c0-0002-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "bootloader"}], {"s": " (the HTML file) loads "}, [":code", {"s": "kernel:core"}], {"s": " from IndexedDB"}]], [":li", [":p", {"s": "The kernel initializes storage, loads styles, renders the safe mode screen as a fallback"}]], [":li", [":p", {"s": "The kernel emits "}, [":code", {"s": "kernel:boot-complete"}]]], [":li", [":p", [":code", {"s": "viewport-manager"}], {"s": " (listening for that event) takes over — loads the rendering engine, resolves the root item from the URL, and renders the full UI"}]], [":li", [":p", {"s": "From here, everything is reactive — item changes trigger targeted re-renders via the event system"}]]], [":p", {"s": "At runtime, the dependency flows downward:"}], [":code-block", {"s": "  Userland (views, libraries, your items)\n      |\n      | uses enriched API (renderItem, navigate, ...)\n      v\n  Viewport (rendering engine, navigation, chrome)\n      |\n      | uses base API (get, set, query, require, events)\n      v\n  Kernel (storage, events, module system)"}], [":h2", {"s": "Where to Go From Here"}], [":ul", [":li", [":p", {"s": "New to Hobson? Start with "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "fa99b548-f705-45fd-8e31-53f4e0818a66"}, {"s": "New Users"}]]], [":li", [":p", {"s": "Want to understand items, types, views? See "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000002"}, {"s": "Core Concepts"}]]], [":li", [":p", {"s": "Want to build views? See "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000004"}, {"s": "Views & Rendering"}]]], [":li", [":p", {"s": "Want to understand events and reactivity? See "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "c0c0c0c0-0006-0000-0000-000000000000"}, {"s": "Event System"}]]], [":li", [":p", {"s": "Want the full architecture? See "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000003"}, {"s": "Architecture Overview"}]]], [":li", [":p", {"s": "Want the philosophy? See "}, [":item-ref", {"s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000001"}, {"s": "Philosophy & Inspirations"}]]]]], "tags": ["bff75873-edb8-412e-81c9-c744e68fe29f", "c0c0c0c0-0085-0000-0000-000000000000"]}, "attachments": []}